Subject Re entrancy of Xlib Known problem From Martin Visser I've found a problem in the use of Xlib functions regarding re I decided to implement an animated cursor using created cursors by calling XDefineCursor from a SIG ALRM signal This is used to indicate we are waiting for a operator request to on a production control system I was redrawing the screen underneath the animated cursor and then restoring the standard cursor when I found dumped core and upon analysis it was when the SIG ALRM handler was called during a XDrawString XDrawString was doing a bcopy presumably an internal structure when the XDefineCursor was Presumably the internal structure that XDrawString was manipulating was not in a stable state and sent XDefineCursor to where it shouldn't have Has anyone else experienced this Is there any official documentation that says you should ensure this doesn't happen Or should bcopy be We are running on SGI Irix with Regards Martin Martin Visser Electrical Software Engineer Engineering Technology Department BHP Steel Slab and Plate Products Division Box Wollongong NSW AUSTRALIA Phone Fax E mail